analysis: The documents in this cluster primarily concern the establishment, modification, and discontinuation of defensive sea areas and airspace reservations for national defense purposes. These areas are often located around naval bases, harbors, and other strategic locations within the United States and its territories. The documents also include regulations for controlling access to these areas, including restrictions on vessel and aircraft navigation. Some documents also relate to labor regulations and tax benefits in designated combat zones.
title: Naval and Airspace Zones for National Defense
